  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (Accepted, W-CON-01)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. This package evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. All 13 credibility factors are addressed; the overall decision record records an Accepted outcome. One factor — Equivalency of input parameters — carries a richly-written qualitative rationale but omits both requiredLevel and achievedLevel, constituting the W-CON-01 inconsistency: the Accepted decision is not fully grounded in structured factor-level evidence.",
  "assuranceLevel": "Low",
  "deviceClass": "Class III",
  "modelRiskLevel": 5,
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/vad-hemolysis-absolute-threshold",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/cou2-vad-hemolysis-cfd-credible",
  "bindsModel": "https://uofa.net/synth/model/cfd-centrifugal-pump-hemolysis-v3",
